# PINFO-194 — explicit Trivy CVE allowlist.
#
# Each entry must carry a CVE ID, the affected component, and a brief
# justification. Re-evaluate every CVE listed here at least once per
# quarter: an entry that has been here for more than 3 months without
# being re-checked is a smell.
#
# Format: one CVE ID per line. Blank lines and lines starting with #
# are ignored. Trivy applies this list AFTER its severity filter.
#
# Two consumers honor this file:
#   - .github/workflows/cd.yml — CRITICAL only, blocks the deploy.
#   - .github/workflows/trivy-scheduled.yml — HIGH + CRITICAL, weekly,
#     fails its own job (notification only, does NOT block deploys).
# So entries here may legitimately be HIGH (kept silent in the weekly
# report when we have a documented reason to accept them temporarily).
#
# Before adding a new entry, prefer overriding the affected library
# version directly via <dependencyManagement> in backend/pom.xml — see
# the Netty BOM override there for the canonical example. Use this
# allowlist only when overriding is impractical (e.g. the fix is in an
# upstream BOM that hasn't been released yet).

# nghttp2-libs CVE-2026-27135 — HTTP/2 DoS via malformed frames.
# Affects nghttp2-libs 1.68.0-r0 in our pinned nginx-unprivileged
# digest (PINFO-196). Fix is in 1.68.1 upstream but the alpine
# rebuild of nginxinc/nginx-unprivileged:stable-alpine has not been
# published yet. Risk for us is bounded:
#   - nginx in our frontend pod only serves static SPA assets — no
#     /api proxy via nginx, that goes through Kong;
#   - the only HTTP/2 exposure we have terminates on Cloudflare's
#     edge, not on this nginx (cloudflared opens a plain HTTP tunnel
#     to the in-cluster ingress).
# To re-check: run `docker buildx imagetools inspect
# nginxinc/nginx-unprivileged:stable-alpine` periodically and bump
# the digest in k8s/frontend/frontend-deployment.yaml +
# frontend/Dockerfile when the new alpine image carries 1.68.1+.
CVE-2026-27135

# quarkus-vertx-http CVE-2026-39852 — HTTP request smuggling via
# malformed Transfer-Encoding header. Affects 3.35.1 (current Quarkus
# BOM after Dependabot bump #89). The upstream fix is in 3.35.1.1,
# which has not been released as a Quarkus platform BOM yet —
# Dependabot will pick it up automatically when it lands.
# Risk for us is bounded:
#   - all /api/* traffic terminates on Kong, which normalises HTTP
#     headers before forwarding, so a smuggled request that enters
#     Cloudflare → cloudflared → Kong is reassembled by Kong before
#     reaching Quarkus;
#   - we don't expose any Quarkus port directly outside the cluster.
# To re-check: when `gh pr list --label dependencies` shows a Quarkus
# bump to 3.35.1.1+, merge it and remove this exception.
CVE-2026-39852

# pgjdbc CVE-2026-42198 — Client-side denial of service when the
# server returns a malformed result-set. Affects org.postgresql:
# postgresql 42.7.10 (the version pinned by Quarkus BOM 3.35.1).
# Fix is in 42.7.11, which is bundled in Quarkus BOM 3.35.1.1+.
# Risk for us is bounded:
#   - the only PostgreSQL we talk to is our own in-cluster Postgres
#     (StatefulSet per service), not a multi-tenant managed DB. An
#     attacker would already need a shell in the cluster to send a
#     malformed payload back to our pods;
#   - even if exploited, the symptom is a connection-pool stall on
#     a single backend service, not RCE or data exfil.
# To re-check: same trigger as CVE-2026-39852 — drop both entries
# together when the Quarkus 3.35.1.1 bump lands.
CVE-2026-42198
